The course consists of the following subjects: ARKA.01.072 Cardiology 6 ECTS, ARKS.01.024 Pulmonary Medicine and Thoracic Surgery 4,5 ECTS ARSK.01.034 Gastroenterology 4 ECTS, ARSK.01.030 Endocrinology 2 ECTS, ARSK.01.039 Rheumatology 3 ECTS, ARSK.01.032 Nephrology 1,5 ECTS, ARHO.02.004 Hematology 2 ECTS, ARSK.03.012 Laboratory medicine 1 ECTS, ARSK.04.001 Infectious diseases 3 ECTS, Geriatrics Basic Course 1 ECTS. See details under the programmes of the abovementioned subjects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide students the basic competency in the field of internal medicine: the scope of common  diseases, their etiology, pathogenesis, diagnosing, differential diagnosis and treatment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the students will be able to 1) specify the symptoms and signs, epidemiology, etiology and pathogenesis of major internal diseases; 2) demonstrate practical skills in acquiring a complete history and physical examination of a medical patient; 3) differentiate between normal and pathology physical, laboratory and radiological findings in internal medicine 4) describe the major indications, adverse events, interactions and contraindications of commonly used drugs in the management of internal diseases
